{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1390853340,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNjM4NzQ5NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/47","origin":"github"},"title":"(lua) sandboxed / parallelised system_load","message":"Currently, system_load allows for pretty much unsupervised \"evil\" behaviors (e.g. glob -\u003e zap_resource etc.), while(true) do done; and similar tom-foolery. \n\nThe suggested change is to have a system_load that can be deferred with a single shallow table as input (spawn new thread, create a new lua context, push table as input, let it execute, when it's finished, trigger a callback with a shallow table as return value) along with a control handle that allows the main thread to kill it off, reduce its resource load or whatever.","files":null}]}